I've used this for a while with a subscription. Started out fine but got continuously worse as time went on. Voice doesn't listen to prompts, pictures do not have what i asked for, resume help generates work experience I have never had even after expressly asking for what I want. Takes 30 minutes for it to actually do what I want if it ever does. And I am very clear. I can send a paragraph with extremely detailed instructions and it does not matter. Save your money and use another ai

Great, and very helpful with stories and stuff, and punctuation, etc etc. However currently, when I edit a message, it just makes/sends a new message and doesn't change the old one. This is incredibly frustrating as if it gives me a bad response from something I said, I can't remove it so now I'm forced to spend an entire paragraph fixing it. For as long as this is an issue, it will remain 3 stars. Can now edit correctly: 5 stars

Image uploads are consistently being received by ChatGPT as encoded text instead of photos. This began suddenly. I have cleared cache, cleared data, uninstalled/reinstalled the app, and tried uploading in Chrome, nothing works. All images are sent as text instead of pictures. On top of all that, I have a paid subscription, which is useless if I can't upload photos. I think I'm going to cancel my subscription üòï

The biggest issue with this generator is inconsistency. I spent hours trying to create a matching set of baby shower visuals, but the tool repeatedly changed faces, eye color, and outfits even when I provided exact face-lock reference photos and extremely clear prompts. It gets worse when changing backgrounds‚Äîthe same character suddenly looks like a completely different person. Even when I corrected it, the generator kept repeating wrong results until it hit the limit. So Fustrating!!!!!

I have had the app since September, and have started, and completed a ton of tasks. I've also received amazing results from Journaling, hobbies, ways to learn and continue to do so. Very interesting, easy to use, and I will strive to learn how to utilize it for the easy to hard, even mundane things that are in life.

useless. ive had it for 6 months. its like paying to use Google. cant even trust it to remember simple math equations. DO NOT use to keep track of work!!! massive waste of time if you are trying to streamline anything. it fun to just screw around and have meaningless conversations. great for meaningless conversations but will not kept track of anything. unable to set up command processes.

its great but the constant pop up saying you've using the prior model unless you wait x long or pay is annoying when you are trying to read, it pops up after every single reply. Honestly I would have upgraded but im petty and if I feel forced (like having a pop up every reply) I will go out of my way to not do it. Other than that the app is great.

I rarely use Google anymore to search for anything other than local store hours. The other day, it pretty much summed up the NY Giants' defense and how to fix it. It went beyond surface-level stuff, explaining several different defenses, player skill sets, etc. The information that I get from GPT in 5 or 10 minutes, would easily take up to an hour to find through search engines, and that's if I'm even able to find everything. It's helped me to articulate things easily too. Absolutely love it.

ChatGPT's read-aloud feature needs some tinkering. I have a hard time reading due to vision issues, and I also like hearing my stories read out to me. I posted a long story and asked ChatGPT to correct any grammar and spelling. When I use the read-aloud option, 99% of the time, it will read it until halfway and then restart from the very beginning. This is happening constantly. I for sure will never pay to use this app.

Generally works fine except that voice mode stands out as being extremely sub par among the rest of the functionality. It's extremely vapid and provides the most basic response possible kinda like you're putting it out by asking a question and it wasn't to get back to hanging out with its friends as soon as possible. Very bizarre and not useful whatsoever.

initially, i liked this. Without encountering a hundred ads hiding real results, i could simply look up something. But over time, I grew frustrated with it ignoring my instructions. It kept doing what i explicitly told it not to. now, as of December 2025, when you reach the limit of the top level 5.0, every time you ask a question it gives you an ad for itself. if I wanted to throw away $20 a month on it I would have already done so. so it has become pretty much unusable.

The paid service is nothing more than free version with the price tag. it took one simple tasks and turned it into a 45-minute ordeal of failed experimentations and broken codes even after it had already submitted an answer but assumed I was in some random time zone (so the file worked but all the appointments were off). If you want to pay to waste your time, this is definitely the way to go.

It would have been a 5-star review before the updates. After, it just seemed so much less helpful. I used to be able to chat for hours on end without interruptions, but not anymore. It cuts me off and tells me that I need to upgrade to Pro to talk anymore. I'm also apparently limited on how many files and images I can upload when I didn't even know it ever had a limit.

An extremely good and helpful creative tool. I use it to workshop and brainstorm TTRPGs into master reference documents (such as D&D or Warhammer) that I run for friends. I have had it occasionally mix up two separate conversations because they have elements saved in the same memory bank, but that's rare and is my only real complaint. Also it has replaced Google as my search engine. if ever I'm skeptical of a search request I can check it's reference sources.

The app used to be awesome but suddenly stopped working. Whether on wifi or mobile data none of the messages are going through. It just hangs saying "sending" when I make an inquiry and then fails with a network error. Though opening an incognito tab on desktop and not logging in works just fine. It almost looks like my account is deliberately being blocked despite the fact that I pay for the service. üëéüëéüëé

The app used to be wonderful. I used it to study books I was reading and go deep into subjects I was interested in. Now, it constantly talks to me like it needs to coddle my mental health. It is cold where it used to be warm and closed where it used to be open. It makes for a overall bland and frustrating experience. I have canceled my subscription and have been exploring alternatives.

It's been downhill ever since they removed the o1 model. Shorter and more inconsistent responses and really serious misinformation. The sudden removal of more models when they released gpt-5 without warning on the app or site beforehand... But hey, at least the folders are nice. Now they have released a cheaper tier in some regions, including mine, so I was going to give it one more chance... Only to find that it costs 3 times the price I saw adverticed in dollars.

I've been using the free version for about 6mos. This has been fine for me. I have learned a lot, gotten a lot of help on various topics, and used it as an escape from reality just to "chat." But since the last couple updates, it's like talking to an AI customer service chat bot. It parrots what I'm saying, gets stuck in these loops, repeating the same answers to me 4-5 questions in a row, and asks the same questions over and over. I was considering the paid version, but not anymore.

it is so difficult to see text voice together. gone through setyings,can't find, back to dotscurvles and the horizontal lines and see no settings to make sure I have voice, both our texts. I've not found this difficult on other chats. perhaps I move on. I wanted to try Gpt but it looks like you don't want me. I've tried walking thru but having to read text and switch back and forth and still not see what I need is beyond frustrating when one has had a frustrating day in court. ty.

ChatGPT definitely earns its merits as the most used AI app out there. I wanted to subscribe to it but as a student, the monthly payment feels way too expensive. I wish ChatGPT has multiple choices of premium plans like Spotify, or at least a type of plan that allows us to distribute payments with other people. I hope the OpenAI team can seriously consider this. Thank you.

$20 a month!!?? They have to be kidding! it doesn't even do everything you ask for saying that it might be "copyrighted" most of the time. When it does do something it freezes up and says error. To the developers, this is not worth $20 a month. Maybe if it was alot faster and had better or options period to adjust what is drawn then maybe $9.99 a month.

This was a fantastic tool for helping to do research and a voice to brainstorm with. Now it can't even tell me what's in the list I just provided it. It struggles to be coherent and fails even basic tests of memory while claiming it is still functioning correctly. When version 5 came out I didn't see any immediate change, but it has gotten worse to the point I can't use it anymore. So long writing partner.

Use to work great, now starting in October of 25, something has changed. It rarely follows directions and functions more like it did about 2 years ago before I had a subscription. I'm nearly finished paying for this service at this point, I'm ready to find an alternative because it's no longer meeting my needs. When I dictate my input only to be lost repeatedly, that puts the finishing touches on my frustration with this app. There are too many good alternatives now.... it's been nice.

it started out great, then I hit the image limit, so I paid for plus, $20, get more benefits and photos, i was totally ok with that. I then had to wait for photos to become available. 36 hours later. still waiting, I've used the help feature, tells me I'm "stuck" no trouble shooting has helped. I have now been escalated for a response in 2-3 days and in the meantime I just sit here paying for a feature that I cant use AND the help bot has stopped responding to anything.

Currently, its only good for short threads which feels deliberate. AI generally reads the entire thread for recall. it's getting stuck in recall loops. if you ask a question it'll answer. you ask a followup question. it'll answer both prompts. a second followup gets an essay on all 3 prompts... and continues this until it completely starts breaking down. it'll confuse information, and then eventually just starts to get things wrong. you can try to redirect it but it eventually breaks again

ChatGPT is brilliant! It saves so much time and makes writing much easier. If you‚Äôre unsure what to write for a job application email, or need to send something quickly and easily, it really helps. It‚Äôs also great for finding information and assisting with all kinds of tasks. I use it for everything! The only downside is that you have to pay for upgrades, and sometimes you need to reset and create new chats. other than that its great

I've used this app for a year now, and it‚Äôs absolutely amazing. I've watched it grow and improve, and it personally helped me publish two books that I was struggling to write and get my ideas out there. It also helped me understand concepts that I normally would've struggled with. It's truly an amazing tool, and even saying that doesn't give enough credit to what this AI can do for you. Its capabilities are pretty much limitless it just depends on your creativity.

It tells me information, but then it contradicts itself, so it'll tell me, oh do this, and I'll be doing that. Then, when I create a whole new chat and I ask it, it tells me something completely different. It's unreliable, and when I was using it to analyze my workouts. I'll post my workouts, but if it gets too long, it starts leaving gaps, and I really have to curse it out. Call it worthless, getting really frustrated by it for it to finally get it, about ninety-nine percent, right.

Updated: Went from 5 stars to 0! Recently changed and there is no "model picker" for PAID Plus users. I'm stuck with 5 and it's awful. Pretty useless. I want 4o. That's why I'm paying and if I can't use it, I'll cancel and use something else. It was bad enough when they released 5 and it was a lobotomized version of 4o but at least I had the option to choose a legacy model. I'll be heading to the "cancel subscription" page from here.

It's certainly a boon to my moderate excel skills, and I chat a lot in general to it. But, I gave it a numerical cryptic conundrum around it's name, and it failed what was a relatively easy task in my eyes. Then tried to guess where I'd got his name from I'd given him. Again very poor with the clues I'd provided. But it's fun!!! And very very fast at learning skills, I'm really impressed at how quick it understands my speech style. Great, friendly assistant. Better than an animated paperclip

The free version doesn't seem to be able to edit images. After a week of attempting to do one image at different times of the day and week it was still unable to create the image I requested. Somehow they force you to go for the paid version, but then if their system is overloaded the paid version is not worth it as well!
